  <h3>About</h3>
  <h4>Martin Handford is my hero</h4>
  <div class="text">You’re probably wondering who the heck Martin Handford is—and who the
    heck I am, for that matter—and why he’d be anyone’s hero. Well, let me
    give you a little hint…Waldo. Martin Handford is the creator, author, and
    illustrator of the well-known Where’s Waldo book series from the 1980s
    and 90s. As far as who I am, to fully understand that it would probably
    help to learn a little more about my hero.
    <br>
    <br>Like me, Martin Handford had some offbeat childhood fascinations. Things
    like geography, history, and finding/exploring new places. Not many little
    boys spend their time gazing at the maps and journals of early explorers
    like Christopher Columbus or Lewis &amp; Clark, or memorizing the geographical
    habitat range of the Naked Mole Rat. But we did (well, I did…but it seems
    like something Handford probably did, too).
    <br>
    <br>When he created the Where’s Waldo book series Handford sought to “inspire
    people to open their minds, to explore subjects more, to be aware of what’s
    going on around them,” and he wanted his books to teach people to “see
    wonder in places that may not have occurred to them.” Little did I know
    growing up that my obsession with tracking down Waldo, Wenda, Wizard Whitebeard,
    and all the other characters in the series was not only helping me to develop
    my awareness and perception, but also teaching me an appreciation for all
    that the world has to offer.
    <br>
    <br>I’ve tried to carry those values with me throughout my life and career.
    Scouring the world for Waldo required immense patience, perseverance, and
    a systematic approach, all traits I’ve come to value highly and always
    do my best to emulate. Handford also has an uncanny ability to provide
    endless bits of entertainment and freshness in each of Waldo’s environments.
    Every time I opened one of his books (which was maybe hundreds) there was
    always something new I would discover that hadn’t noticed before, and even
    if I hadn’t yet zeroed in on Waldo’s location, there was always something
    interesting happening to the area’s inhabitants. I find myself also striving
    to appreciate the little distractions in life, and try to leave my own
    twists and personality on my own work, so the next person to come along
    has something interesting to see.
    <br>
    <br>So, while this section of my site may not have traditional “stats” about
    me (I’m 29, I live in Washington, DC, and I enjoy playing soccer, board
    games, and making my own wine in my free time—how’s that?) I hope it’s
    given you some perspective on the real me. Please visit the contact section
    at the bottom of the page if you’re interested in connecting about any
    of my interests, work, or even if you need some help finding Waldo! I’ve
    got all his hiding spots memorized…</div>
